Sentencas: Pulsed Laser Deposition (PLD) was used to prepare thin films with the nominal composition La0.58Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF).
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: The thin film microstructure was investigated as a function of PLD deposition parameters such as: substrate temperature, ambient gas pressure, target-to-substrate distance, laser fluence and frequency.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: It was found that the ambient gas pressure and the substrate temperature are the key PLD process parameters determining the thin film micro- and nanostructure.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: A map of the LSCF film nanostructures is presented as a function of substrate temperature (25-700 degrees C) and oxygen background pressure (0.013-0.4 mbar), with film structures ranging from fully dense to highly porous.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: Fully crystalline, dense, and crack-free LSCF films with a thickness of 300 nm were obtained at an oxygen pressure lower than 0.13 mbar at a temperature of 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: The obtained knowledge on the structure allows for tailoring of perovskite thin film nanostructure, e.g., for solid oxide fuel cell cathodes.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: A simple geometrical model is proposed, allowing estimation of the catalytic active surface area of the prepared thin films.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition

Sentencas: It is shown that voids at columnar grain boundaries can result in an increase of the surface area by approximately 25 times, when compared to dense flat films.
Titulo: Tailoring of LaxSr1-xCoyFe1-yO3-δ Nanostructure by Pulsed Laser Deposition
